<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.4.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="http://localhost:4000/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="http://localhost:4000/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2026-07-12T23:24:33+00:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/feed.xml</id><title type="html">=][=</title><subtitle>A hobby blog covering Warhammer, painting, conversions, and grimdark projects.</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Too Many Eyes</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2026/07/11/too-many-eyes.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Too Many Eyes" /><published>2026-07-11T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-07-11T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2026/07/11/too-many-eyes</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2026/07/11/too-many-eyes.html"><![CDATA[<p><img src="/assets/img/too-many-eyes.png" alt="Too Many Eyes" /></p>

<hr />

<p style="text-align:center">How many eyes is too many eyes?</p>

<p style="text-align:center">However many eyes the thing had.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">They blinked, they rolled, they winked.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Some bled, some wept, some blind.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Too many eyes.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Unfocused, wandering, wondering.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Too many eyes.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Focused now, many eyes are one eye.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">They see me.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Too many eyes see through me.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">They do not wander.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">I dare not move or speak.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">It speaks from a mouth that I cannot see.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">It tells me that it sees me.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">I cannot move or speak.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Something silver, something sharp, something quick.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Now I see, with too many eyes.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="horror" /><category term="poetry" /><category term="grimdark" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/too-many-eyes.png" /><media:content medium="image" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/too-many-eyes.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Rest in Peace: John Blanche</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2026/07/08/rip-john-blanche.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Rest in Peace: John Blanche" /><published>2026-07-08T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-07-08T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2026/07/08/rip-john-blanche</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2026/07/08/rip-john-blanche.html"><![CDATA[<blockquote>
  <p>The Bell of Lost Souls will now ring 40,000 times.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>There are no words to truly convey the impact that John Blanche had on the world of Warhammer and miniature painting. His art, commonly referred to by the community as “Blanchitsu”, pioneered the “grim dark” style that defined the early editions of Warhammer 40,000, and would be the pillar upon which everything else was built. It’s a reductive method of painting that uses a fairly sparse colour pallete, mostly focusing on earthy tones such as reds, oranges, and browns, but blended in a way that instantly tells a story. It’s an instantly recognisable style, especially for those of us who have been around the hobby for a long time. For some of us his art was what drew us in in the first place.</p>

<p>Without knowing it, I’ve been exposed to John’s art since my childhood, all the early edition 40k box arts are John’s pieces. The bright red of the Blood Angels on the Second edition box, to the iconic Black Templars art used on the box of the Third edition, his iconic depiction of The Emperor of Mankind, the iconic Sister of Battle stood on the hill with her foot on a skull, his incredible work on the Mordheim rulebook… the list just goes on and on.</p>

<p>John Blanche will forever live on through his art and the inspiration he has provided for others. A true legend.</p>

<hr />

<p><img src="/assets/img/blanche-tech-priest.png" alt="Rest in Peace John Blanche" /></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="grimdark" /><category term="blanchitsu" /><category term="warhammer" /><category term="featured" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A short tribute to painting legend John Blanche, who passed away this year.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/blanche1.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/blanche1.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">No Longer</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2026/06/28/no-longer.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="No Longer" /><published>2026-06-28T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-06-28T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2026/06/28/no-longer</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2026/06/28/no-longer.html"><![CDATA[<p style="text-align:center">I see myself through my own eyes.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">But they are no longer my eyes</p>

<p style="text-align:center">This is no longer my body</p>

<p style="text-align:center">These are no longer my legs</p>

<p style="text-align:center">These are no longer my arms</p>

<p style="text-align:center; color:red">I need to scream</p>

<p style="text-align:center">But this is no longer my mouth</p>

<p style="text-align:center">The arms that are no longer mine move</p>

<p style="text-align:center">They have moved like this before</p>

<p style="text-align:center">They will move like this again</p>

<p style="text-align:center">They will move like this forever</p>

<p style="text-align:center">I see this with eyes that are no longer mine</p>

<p style="text-align:center">I remember, with a memory that is no longer my own</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="horror" /><category term="grimdark" /><category term="poetry" /><category term="featured" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I see myself through my own eyes.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/no-longer.png" /><media:content medium="image" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/no-longer.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Test Post 7</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2026/01/01/test-post-4.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Test Post 7" /><published>2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2026/01/01/test-post-4</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2026/01/01/test-post-4.html"><![CDATA[<p>This is test post 1.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="test" /><category term="featured" /><category term="coca" /><category term="cola" /><category term="40k" /><category term="darkmech" /><category term="admech" /><category term="chips" /><category term="yourmum" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[This is test post 1.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/blanche2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/blanche2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Test Post 6</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2026/01/01/test-post-5.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Test Post 6" /><published>2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2026/01/01/test-post-5</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2026/01/01/test-post-5.html"><![CDATA[<p>This is test post 1.</p